com.maxleap

类 MLObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.maxleap.MLObject
  • 直接已知子类:
    MLInstallation, MLUser

    public class MLObject
extends Object
    The MLObject is a local representation of data that can be saved and retrieved from the ML cloud.

        public static void registerSubclass(Class<? extends MLObject> subclass)
        Registers a custom subclass type with the ML SDK, enabling strong-typing of those MLObjects whenever they appear. Subclasses must specify the MLClassName annotation and have a default constructor.

      • setObjectId

        public void setObjectId(String objectId)
        Setter for the object id. In general you do not need to use this. However, in some cases this can be convenient. For example, if you are serializing a MLObject yourself and wish to recreate it, you can use this to recreate the MLObject exactly.
        参数:
        objectId - the objectId

      • getObjectId

        public String getObjectId()
        Accessor to the object id. An object id is assigned as soon as an object is saved to the server. The combination of a className and an objectId uniquely identifies an object in your application.
        返回:
        the objectId

      • getCreatedAt

        public Date getCreatedAt()
        This reports time as the server sees it, so that if you create a MLObject, then wait a while, and then call save(), the creation time will be the time of the first save() call rather than the time the object was created locally.
        返回:
        The first time this object was saved on the server.

      • getUpdatedAt

        public Date getUpdatedAt()
        This reports time as the server sees it, so that if you make changes to a MLObject, then wait a while, and then call save(), the updated time will be the time of the save() call rather than the time the object was changed locally.
        返回:
        The last time this object was updated on the server.

        public void addUnique(String key,

      • addAllUnique

        public void addAllUnique(String key,
                Collection<?> values)
        Atomically adds the objects contained in a Collection to the array associated with a given key, only adding elements which are not already present in the array. The position of the insert is not guaranteed.
        参数:
        key - The key.
        values - The objects to add.

      • removeAll

        public void removeAll(String key,
             Collection<?> values)
        Atomically removes all instances of the objects contained in a Collection from the array associated with a given key. To maintain consistency with the Java Collection API, there is no method removing all instances of a single object. Instead, you can call MLObject.removeAll(key, Arrays.asList(value)).
        参数:
        key - The key.
        values - The objects to remove.

      • isDataAvailable

        public boolean isDataAvailable()
        Gets whether the MLObject has been fetched.
        返回:
        true if the MLObject is new or has been fetched. false otherwise.

      • create

        public static <T extends MLObject> T create(String className)
        Creates a new MLObject based upon a class name. If the class name is a special type (e.g. for MLUser), then the appropriate type of MLObject is returned.
        参数:
        className - The class of object to create.
        返回:
        A new MLObject for the given class name.

      • create

        public static <T extends MLObject> T create(Class<T> subclass)
        Creates a new MLObject based upon a subclass type. Note that the object will be created based upon the MLClassName of the given subclass type.
        类型参数:
        T - a class extends MLObject
        参数:
        subclass - The class of object to create.
        返回:
        A new MLObject based upon the class name of the given subclass type.

      • createWithoutData

        public static <T extends MLObject> T createWithoutData(String className,
                                       String objectId)
        Creates a reference to an existing MLObject for use in creating associations between MLObjects. Calling MLObject.isDataAvailable() on this object will return false until MLDataManage.fetchInBackground() has been called. No network request will be made.
        参数:
        className - the class name
        objectId - the objectId
        返回:
        a MLObject

      • createWithoutData

        public static <T extends MLObject> T createWithoutData(Class<T> subClass,
                                       String objectId)
        Creates a reference to an existing MLObject for use in creating associations between MLObjects. Calling MLObject.isDataAvailable() on this object will return false until MLObject.fetchIfNeeded() or MLObject.refresh() has been called. No network request will be made.
        参数:
        subClass - The MLObject subclass to create.
        objectId - The object id for the referenced object.
        返回:
        A MLObject without data.
